goals.question: What is the distribution of bacteria based on their Gram Staining?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of Gram Staining vs Count of Bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the proportion of bacteria that are Gram-positive or Gram-negative.

goals.question: What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin resistance in bacteria?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of Penicillin vs Streptomycin resistance
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying if there is any correlation between the resistance of bacteria to Penicillin and Streptomycin.

goals.question: Which genus of bacteria has the highest resistance to Neomycin?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of Genus vs Neomycin resistance
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the genus of bacteria that has the highest resistance to Neomycin, which can be useful in developing targeted treatments.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Penicillin resistance among Gram-positive bacteria?
goals.visualization: Histogram of Penicillin resistance for Gram-positive bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the distribution of Penicillin resistance among Gram-positive bacteria, which can be useful in developing targeted treatments.

goals.question: What is the relationship between Streptomycin resistance and Gram Staining in bacteria?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Streptomycin resistance for Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying if there is any difference in the distribution of Streptomycin resistance between Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gram_staining_counts = data['Gram_Staining'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=gram_staining_counts.index, y=gram_staining_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Gram Staining')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Bacteria')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bacteria based on their Gram Staining?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', y='Streptomycin', hue='Genus', style='Gram_Staining')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin resistance in bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Genus & Gram Staining', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Genus', y='Neomycin', data=data, ci=None)
    max_resistance = data.groupby('Genus')['Neomycin'].max().max()
    plt.axhline(max_resistance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Resistance: {max_resistance:.2f}')
    plt.title('Which genus of bacteria has the highest resistance to Neomycin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gram_positive_data = data[data['Gram_Staining'] == 'positive']
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=gram_positive_data, x='Penicillin', hue='Genus', multiple='stack', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin resistance among Gram-positive bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin Resistance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Genus', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='Gram_Staining', y='Streptomycin', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Streptomycin resistance and Gram Staining in bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Gram Staining', labels=['Gram-positive', 'Gram-negative'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
